<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WESTWOOD; DRIVER HELD AFTER CRASH KILLS 1, HURTS 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A speeding Jeep overturned on Sunset Boulevard early Tuesday, killing one 
passenger and injuring four others, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, Paul Hadley, 23, of Westwood, was booked on suspicion of felony 
manslaughter and held on $35,000 bail, said Los Angeles Police Officer David 
Kennedy.Police said they suspect Hadley was intoxicated. 
</P>
<P>
 A 23-year-old man whose name was withheld pending notification of relatives 
died at UCLA Medical Center, Kennedy said. 
</P>
<P>
 Three other men and a woman, all in their 20s, suffered injuries that were not 
believed to be life-threatening, Kennedy said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said the Jeep, estimated to be traveling at more than 60 m.p.h. -- 
with the top and sides removed -- was westbound on Sunset Boulevard at Bellagio 
Road about 2:25 a.m. The driver apparently lost control of the vehicle and it 
overturned, tossing out five passengers, LAPD Sgt. Doug Laird said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hadley, who was uninjured, was the only one in the car wearing a seat belt and 
was not thrown from the vehicle, Laird said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
