<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY: CAFE & DELI: JUST PLAIN GOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Many shoppers begin or end an outing on San Pedro's Pacific Avenue at the San 
Pedro Cafe & Deli in downtown San Pedro. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cafe is a plain place. On one wall, behind the 10-seat counter, hangs a 
poster from the movie "My Little Chickadee" featuring Mae West and W. C. 
Fields. Opposite, nearly hidden behind high-backed vinyl booths on a shelf 
lined with marine artifacts, is a plate commemorating the Three Stooges. 
</P>
<P>
 If you happen to be going out for a long day of shopping (or boating, for that 
matter), you might consider stocking up on the Cafe's manhandler breakfast 
($5.95): two eggs, two sausages, two strips of bacon, two pancakes, a ham steak 
and hash browns. However, most customers go for the biggest sellers -- omelets. 
There is a shrimp omelet ($5.95), mixed with bay shrimp, mushrooms and onions 
and topped with a hollandaise sauce, and an Italian model ($5.95) that features 
sausage, ricotta, mozzarella and marinara sauce. 
</P>
<P>
 Until 11 a.m., the Cafe features a $2.99 special of two eggs; a choice of 
turkey bacon, sausage or turkey sausage; and a choice of buttermilk pancakes, 
beans and tortillas, bagel and cream cheese, or biscuits and gravy, which 
should cover fans of Midwestern, Mexican, Jewish and Southern breakfasts. 
</P>
<P>
 For lunch, the one-third-pound freshly ground hamburgers ($4.25 to $5.25) take 
over the best-seller list. Served on a wheat bun, they come with pasta salad or 
french fries. Among the familiar list of sandwiches is meatloaf ($5.25) with 
jack cheese and grilled sourdough, an open-faced hot turkey with mashed 
potatoes and gravy ($4.95), chicken or tuna salad ($5.65) and chicken fried 
steak ($5.95). 
</P>
<P>
 The San Pedro Cafe & Deli is at 605 S. Pacific Ave . , San Pedro. (310) 
547-0961. Open Monday through Saturday 7 a.m. to 4 p.m., and Sunday 7 a.m. to 3 
p.m. MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
