<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SAN FERNANDO; VOLUNTEERS TO CLEAN PARK'S PLAYGROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Volunteers are needed to help with a community cleanup of the Las Palmas Park 
tot lot Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 "They should bring their work gloves," said San Fernando Recreation and 
Community Service Director Ed Montan.Volunteers will sand and reseal the wooden 
playground equipment, which has splintered over the years. 
</P>
<P>
 The cleanup project starts at 9 a.m. and will wrap up about 5 p.m. Volunteers 
can work just an hour or two or work all day. 
</P>
<P>
 "If we can get 50 to 75 people to show up, that will be great," Montan said. 
</P>
<P>
 The tot lot playground, which has swings, interconnecting tunnels, ramps, 
bridges and ladders, was built in 1991 by volunteers after a $45,000 
fund-raising campaign. It is located at 505 S. Huntington St., San Fernando. ED 
BOND 
</P>
