 Ken Turner, Ohio State assistant coach,suffered from a heart attack while 
jogging and was in critical condition at Grant Medical Center in Columbus.He 
was stricken while running near his home in suburban Westerville. . . . Shareef 
Abdur-Rahim of Wheeler High School in Atlanta, one of the nation's top college 
prospects, said he will attend California. The 6-foot-10 center, a Muslim, said 
that he chose Cal over Georgia Tech, Georgetown and Arkansas largely because he 
felt comfortable with the large Islamic population there. Hockey 
</P>
