<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: PASADENA; COUNCIL IS UNANIMOUS IN OPPOSING PROP. 187 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council on Monday voted unanimously to oppose Proposition 187, which 
would deny most public services to illegal immigrants if approved by voters 
Nov. 8. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier Monday, representatives of the Pasadena Unified School District and 
various organizations, including El Centro de Accion Social and the Pasadena 
chapter of the National Assn. for the Advancement of Colored People, held a 
press conference on the steps of City Hall to voice their opposition to the 
controversial measure. 
</P>
<P>
 The community leaders said they oppose Proposition 187 because, among other 
things, it would require teachers to report children whom they suspect to be 
illegal immigrants. Those children would then be barred from attending public 
school and would end up on the streets, the opponents said. 
</P>
<P>
 Supporters of the measure, including Assemblyman Richard Mountjoy (R-Arcadia), 
contend California taxpayers are spending too much money on services for 
illegal immigrants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
