<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: SAN MARINO; OFFICERS PLAN PICKET OF CITY HALL OVER PAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Members of the San Marino Police Officers Assn. were planning to picket City 
Hall this afternoon, demanding a 9% pay raise, the association's spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The force's 26 sworn personnel have not had a raise in two years, said Sgt. 
Mark Harvey, adding that his police force is the lowest-paid force in the San 
Gabriel Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The association was at an impasse with the city Sept. 15, Harvey said. 
</P>
<P>
 Assistant City Manager Debbie Bell said the city has offered a two-year 
package that includes a 7% pay increase and performance raises. 
</P>
