<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: ALHAMBRA; INTERIM FIRE CHIEF TO ACCEPT PERMANENT JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Interim Fire Chief James A. Ballard, a department veteran, will officially 
accept the Fire Chief badge permanently today. 
</P>
<P>
 Ballard, 47, was appointed to replace Fire Chief Raymond Brooks on Sept. 12. 
He has served as interim chief since April, when Brooks became San Jose's fire 
chief. 
</P>
<P>
 "Over his 25 years of service to the Alhambra community, and in the past 
several months as interim fire chief, Ballard has proved a skilled firefighter 
and able leader," City Manager Julio Fuentes said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ballard joined the department in 1969 after three years in the U.S. Army. He 
has served as the department's fire marshal and as a battalion chief. 
</P>
<P>
 The ceremony will be held at Headquarters Fire Station, 301 1st St., Alhambra. 
</P>
