<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; PETS: EAR TAGS OFFERED TO IDENTIFY LOST CATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals/Southern 
California Humane Society has initiated a new method to identify lost cats: ear 
tags. 
</P>
<P>
 The group says piercing a cat's ear is a painless procedure and is safer for 
active felines, which face the risk of strangling themselves with an 
identification collar as they roam outdoors. 
</P>
<P>
 The tag, a stud disk with two phone numbers engraved on it, is available at 
the Los Angeles SPCA/SCHS, 5026 W. Jefferson Blvd. near La Brea Avenue, for 
$12. 
</P>
<P>
 The procedure is not recommended for dogs because there are too many blood 
vessels and nerves in their ears, the group said. 
</P>
<P>
 For an appointment, call (213) 730-5300. 
</P>
</TEXT>
