<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOSPITAL MAKES FULL RECOVERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When the dust cleared after the Jan. 17 earthquake, St. John's Hospital and 
Health Center looked like a bad accident. The north wing of the 1940s structure 
was lost, and only outpatient services have been available for the last eight 
months.Now, the historic building has been patched up and is ready to reopen. 
The community will celebrate with a big "Bouncing Back" party Saturday, 11 
a.m.-3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Billy Vera and the Beaters will perform a free concert. Numerous sports 
figures -- including Doug Christie and James Worthy of the Lakers, pro 
volleyball player Gabrielle Reece and Kelvin Hildreth, Sterling Forbes and 
Jeffrey Dollison of the Harlem Globetrotters -- will lend their support. 
</P>
<P>
 A parade, starting at Olympic School at 11th Street and Arizona Avenue, kicks 
off the event at 11 a.m. Among the many marchers following a one-mile route to 
St. John's will be the Cardiac Physicians Drill Team, the Santa Monica High 
Marching Band, L.A. Polo Club and Boy Scouts. A food court at the hospital will 
offer In-N-Out Burger, Ben & Jerry's ice cream and more. 
</P>
<P>
 Sports clinics include slam-dunk and three-point contests, led by the pro 
ballplayers; volleyball demonstrations by pro players Reece, Linda Chisholm and 
Linda Hanley. Also: games and free health screenings. The event is free. (310) 
829-8016. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
