<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIDBITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEO SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top chefs team up to form culinary organization and to prepare special monthly 
dinners. Some of Ventura County's top chefs last week teamed with some of the 
best from Santa Barbara County and one from Malibu to form the Central Coast 
Culinaire Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Local association members include Sandy Smith of Rosarito Beach Cafe 
(Ventura), Yvan Lampron of Ojai Valley Inn (Ojai), Randy Saito of the Hyatt 
Westlake Plaza (Westlake Village), Gael Lecolley of Wheeler's Hot Springs 
(Ojai), Francois Milet of The Tower Club (Oxnard), Anthony Gillespie of 
Pastabilities (Camarillo), Kevin Sherrie of Las Posas Country Club (Camarillo), 
Ted Growi of L'Auberge (Ojai) and Brian Barker of McCarthy's (Camarillo). 
</P>
<P>
 The 16 members of the CCCA, organized by Robert Lopez, general manager of The 
Tower Club, will share ideas, and on a monthly basis team up to prepare 
four-course meals for the public. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's a lot of camaraderie among them, no jealousy," Lopez said. "They just 
want to have fun and let the people of Ventura County know who they are." 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez said each month a different chef will host a dinner at his or her 
restaurant, and the others will pitch in. Chefs will rotate from table to table 
during the meals to meet with the guests. Cost of these dinners will be $65. 
</P>
<P>
 The first joint dinner will be held Tuesday at The Tower Club, with only Tower 
Club members invited. After that, the meals will be open to the general public, 
so stay tuned. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chefs association member Randy Saito and his Hyatt Westlake staff of 26 cooks 
this month have begun to offer an International Lunch Buffet at the hotel's La 
Terraza restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 Each weekday from 11:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. cuisine from a different region of the 
world will be featured, with menus changing periodically. The lineup is 
American food on Mondays, Mexican on Tuesdays, followed by Asian, Italian and 
South Pacific/Caribbean fare. Cost is $7.75, down from the previous $9.75 
buffet price. The Hyatt is located at 800 S. Westlake Blvd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
