<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 IRS Sets New Rules on Electronic Filing: In an effort to crack down on fraud, 
the Internal Revenue Service is requiring professional tax preparers who file 
returns electronically to submit to fingerprinting and a credit check.The new 
procedures, detailed in a 47-page regulation issued Tuesday, also require 
preparers with access to IRS computers to be at least 21 years old and either 
U.S. citizens or permanent resident immigrants. The action, intended to screen 
out preparers with criminal records and severe financial problems, is effective 
immediately. It was taken after congressional hearings spotlighted unscrupulous 
preparers who claimed false refunds on clients' electronic returns. 
</P>
