<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERSONAL VIEW: EXECUTIVE TRAVEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Name: Alex Auerbach 
</P>
<P>
 * Position: Public relations consultant 
</P>
<P>
 Many business travelers use laptop computers, which are easily lost or stolen 
in the rush of a business trip. Should an IBM-compatible laptop simply be lost, 
the finder can be encouraged to return it with a screen message included in the 
AUTOEXEC.BAT file. 
</P>
<P>
 The message should display the name of the computer's owner, along with an 
address and phone number (with international dialing codes if traveling 
overseas) and an offer of a reward for the return of the system. 
</P>
<P>
 Including the message in the AUTOEXEC file will ensure that it is displayed as 
soon as the machine is turned on -- which is what someone who finds a computer 
is likely to do. 
</P>
<P>
 Identification tags and labels on the computer and case are helpful, but they 
can fall off, or the computer may be misplaced without its carrying case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Infobox; Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
