<P>
 The city will spend $5,200 for the transportation of seniors participating in 
the Senior Meals and Services program. 
</P>
<P>
 About 18 residents aged 60 and older are taken from their homes Monday through 
Friday to the Youth Center on Oak Street for the nutrition program and to 
participate in bingo and other activities. 
