<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SANTA ANA; GUNSHOT PUTS MAN IN CRITICAL CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TAMMERLIN DRUMMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 22-year-old man was listed in critical condition Wednesday with wounds 
suffered when he was shot in the chest by unidentified attackers while driving 
his car along South Newhope Boulevard late Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin Rivas of Santa Ana lost control of the vehicle and crashed into a 
tree after he was shot once with a semiautomatic handgun, police Lt. Dave Petko 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe the attack was gang-related but have no witnesses. Petko said a 
small white car was seen speeding away from the scene after the 9:05 p.m. 
assault. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were called to the 300 block of South Newhope by residents who heard 
gunfire. When they arrived, Petko said, Rivas was slumped in the driver's seat, 
bleeding from the gunshot wound. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were still seeking information Wednesday on the identity and 
whereabouts of Rivas' attackers. TAMMERLIN DRUMMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
