<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN, 24, IS STRUCK, KILLED BY MOTORCYCLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 24-year-old woman was struck and killed by a motorcycle Wednesday morning as 
she walked across East Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Carena Munos was crossing at Balsam Avenue, outside the crosswalk, about 6 
a.m. when she was hit, police spokesman Chuck O'Connor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Munos suffered serious head and chest injuries and was transported to UCI 
Medical Center in Orange, where she died two hours later. 
</P>
<P>
 The motorcycle rider was not injured or cited by police, O'Connor said. The 
cause of the accident is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
