<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: TUSTIN GUARD GOTTLIEB PICKS NOTRE DAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Doug Gottlieb, a point guard at Tustin High, made an oral commitment to attend 
Notre Dame, he announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Gottlieb, a 6-foot, 180-pound senior, was a Times all-county selection and the 
Sea View League boys' basketball most valuable player last season after 
averaging 19.7 points and nine assists. 
</P>
<P>
 "I loved the campus at Notre Dame," Gottlieb said. "I like the idea of going 
to play in the Big East as a freshman." 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame, which plays as an independent, will join the Big East for 
basketball in the 1995-96 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Gottlieb, who also has a 3.6 grade-point average, visited Notre Dame Sept. 
9-11 and told Coach John MacLeod of his intention to sign with the Fighting 
Irish Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Gottlieb canceled trips to Connecticut, Florida, Michigan State and Virginia. 
He also considered UCLA and Stanford. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
