<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UCI WOMEN SHUT OUT SAN BERNARDINO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UC Irvine women's soccer team recorded its second consecutive victory 
Wednesday, shutting out Cal State San Bernardino, 3-0, in a nonconference game 
at Anteater Field. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior co-captain Lori Muzzonigro opened the scoring at the 4:48 mark on a 
deflection off a Coyote defender in the box. 
</P>
<P>
 With 10 minutes remaining in the half, sophomore reserve Keelyn Healy scored 
the Anteaters' second goal on a pass from senior Kim Franzen. 
</P>
<P>
 UCI finished the scoring at the 68-minute mark, when freshman Tracie Manz 
headed a cross from senior Jenni Tanaka. Manz leads the team in scoring with 
three goals and two assists.  
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore goalkeeper Stephanie Boes recorded her fourth shutout of the season, 
making three saves. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 5, The Master's 2 -- Cindy LeClair scored two goals for visiting 
Chapman, which improves to 5-2. Jen Wagner, Beverly Tibbo and Amy Feniello 
scored the other three goals for the Panthers. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara 4, Southern California College 0 -- Jeff Johnson had one goal 
and two assists for host UCSB (3-3). Brent Rogers had 10 saves for SCC (3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 3, Claremont-Mudd-Scripps 0 -- Elaini Kollias had 11 kills for host 
Concordia (10-4), which won, 15-7, 15-12, 15-11. 
