<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY and T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With backup right tackle Darryl Ashmore out with a sprained medial collateral 
knee ligament, rookie Wayne Gandy will back up both left tackle Clarence Jones 
and right tackle Jackie Slater. 
</P>
<P>
 Gandy, a first-round draft pick who has struggled in the first three games, 
got most of his work in practice at right tackle. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was a swing tackle at Auburn so I'm not foreign to the position," said 
Gandy, whom the Rams took 16th overall in last April's draft. "We're pretty 
thin right now, so everybody's having to chip in and learn all the positions. 
Coach says he's going to get me out there, hopefully." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 As expected, the Rams re-signed wide receiver Todd Kinchen and put left guard 
Keith Loneker (fallen left arch) on the injured-reserve list. The Rams also 
worked out offensive lineman Roosevelt Patterson, a free-agent from Alabama. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 William White, the Chiefs' starting free safety, suffered a sprained ankle and 
is questionable for Sunday's game. . . . Kansas City quarterback Joe Montana is 
12-7 as a San Francisco starter against the Rams, and the Chiefs are 7-0 at 
Arrowhead Stadium with Montana as their starter. . . . The Rams lead the 
series, 3-1, and are 2-0 at Arrowhead Stadium. MIKE REILLEY and T.J. SIMERS 
