<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: 16-VEHICLE PILEUP INJURES 1, JAMS TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A chain-reaction, 16-vehicle pileup caused one minor injury and a long traffic 
tie-up on the westbound Ventura Freeway on Wednesday morning, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The problem started about 5:20 a.m. when a motorist made an unsafe lane change 
on the freeway's downhill grade near Las Virgenes Road, and five cars hit each 
other, said California Highway Patrol Officer Dave King. 
</P>
<P>
 As other motorists tried to avoid that wreck, they caused six other accidents 
as cars rear-ended each other in the fog, King said. 
</P>
<P>
 The only reported injury occurred when one of the drivers, who was not wearing 
a seat belt, hit her head against her windshield, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 That motorist was not hospitalized, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two lanes of traffic were blocked for more than an hour as authorities cleared 
up the accident, King said. TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</TEXT>
