<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAIRPLEX; STEWARDS SUSPEND JOCKEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ROBLEDO, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jockey Brian Long has been suspended indefinitely by Fairplex Park stewards 
because he failed to appear at a hearing Monday to answer questions about a 
sexual harassment charge. 
</P>
<P>
 The charge was made by female jockey Joy Scott, who told stewards that Long 
was often grabbing at her and once danced naked on a stool in front of her. 
</P>
<P>
 Long and Antonio Castanon engaged in a whip-to-whip fight during the stretch 
run of a race at Hollywood Park last summer. After the race, Long went after 
Castanon and the two went at it again in the middle of the track. 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't do this to create more problems for him, but it was getting worse," 
Scott said. "He just wouldn't listen. He would grab my rear and I would have to 
slap his hand away, but that wouldn't stop him from doing it again. 
</P>
<P>
 "I know that men act like men and I can let a lot of things go by, but not 
this. I've been riding since 1981 and always have been respected by the male 
riders. When he danced naked on the stool, that was the icing on the cake." 
</P>
<P>
 The day after she made the complaint, Scott claimed Long verbally abused her 
and spit in her face. 
</P>
<P>
 Steward David Samuel said that Long called the track Tuesday, but did not 
indicate when he would return. 
</P>
<P>
 "Until he appears, he will remain suspended," Samuel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Long could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Notes 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Fleet, ridden by Scott Stevens, caught and passed 4-5 favorite Candid 
Moments in deep stretch to post a neck victory in Wednesday's $110,000 Barretts 
Debutante, the 6 1/2-furlong 11th-race feature for 2-year-old fillies who were 
offered for sale at a Barretts auction. Corey Nakatani sent Candid Moments to 
the lead going around the first turn, but Artica, ridden by Fernando 
Valenzuela, challenged for the lead during the entire backstretch to set the 
race up for Tina Fleet's stretch run. . . . Post time for the first race will 
be 1 p.m., beginning Saturday and will remain at that time for the remainder of 
the meet 
</P>
</TEXT>
