in 41 carries. Golf 
</P>
<P>
 A trio of Westlake High players finished in the top 20 over the weekend at the 
Lake Tahoe Junior Golf Classic at the Genoa Lakes Golf Club in Genoa, Nev. 
</P>
<P>
 Ross Fulgentis of Westlake Village was the top area player with a 36-hole 
total of 144, good for a share of fifth place. He finished six shots off the 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake teammates Brandon DiTullio finished tied for ninth at 146, and Matt 
McCrite tied for 20th at 150. Darren Angel of Northridge finished tied for 16th 
at 149. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Semelsberger of Newhall finished in a tie for 31st at 152, Ben Cherney 
of Encino tied for 37th at 153 and David Trovato of Valencia tied for 39th at 
154. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Girls' participation in high school sports in the Southern Section has 
increased 28.3% over the past two school years, according to figures recently 
released by the section. Boys' participation increased 8.7% over the same 
period. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' sport with the greatest increase in participation was soccer, which 
increased 22.6%. The number of girls playing 11-man football increased from 14 
to 71. 
</P>
<P>
 The results are based on a survey the section distributed to its 1,148 member 
schools. The section received responses from 93% of the schools. 
</P>
