<TEXT>
<P>
 Longtime resident Frank Chang has been appointed to the city Planning 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 Chang, 49, is a member of the ABC Unified School District Affirmative Action 
Committee, the president of Chinese Parents for Whitney High School Excellence 
and director of student activity at the Cerritos Chinese School.He has lived in 
Cerritos for 17 years. 
</P>
<P>
 He is a senior engineer with the Northrop Grumman Corp.'s aircraft division in 
Hawthorne. 
</P>
<P>
 After coming to the United States from Taiwan in 1970, Chang earned a master's 
degree in mechanical engineering in 1973 from Utah State University. 
</P>
<P>
 He was appointed by Mayor Pro Tem Grace Hu to complete the term of Titus Yen, 
who recently resigned because of work obligations. The term ends in 1996. JOHN 
CANALIS 
