<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: PICO RIVERA; TEMPORARY STREET BARRICADE GETS OK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN D. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has approved a temporary barricade on Manzanar Avenue to stem 
the flow of traffic off of heavily traveled Telegraph Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Numerous drivers have been using Manzanar, a residential street, to avoid the 
crowded intersection of Rosemead Boulevard and Telegraph Road, and residents 
along Manzanar complained that heavy traffic was unsafe.A recent survey found 
that 768 vehicles a day used Manzanar, compared to a range of 103 to 240 cars 
per day on similar streets. 
</P>
<P>
 Manzanar will be barricaded north of Telegraph in early October for a 
two-month trial period, officials said. Three cross streets north of the 
barricade will provide access to the neighborhood.  
</P>
<P>
 Resident Richard Salcido praised the decision. "There are too many cars 
driving down here too fast," he said. JOHN D. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
